From Larry Landwehr Subject Corel Draw or Harvard Draw My wife wants to publish a She's no artist so she intends to use comercial clipart and customise it a bit by drawing a circle or a box around it We have MSPublisher for manipulating text but it is not suitable for doing much with graphics so she needs a more specialised Right now she's looking at Corel Draw and Harvard There seem to be more books in the stores on Corel than on Harvard so she's inclined to go with Corel on the basis of Can anyone give us an informed opinion on which package would be more suitable or if there is an even better alternative available If this is a FAQ please withhold the flames and just send the location of the FAQ Three PS's Is it ok to use clip art from Harvard Draw or whatever for commercial purposes We have a dpi Laser Jet What would be a good scanner for reading in paper clipart How about someone starting up a newsgroup on desktop publishing if one doesn't exist